@node Description "What is TimeEvent?"

With  the TimeEvent Preference  Editor you can  control the execution times of a
list of programs.

You can popup a requester to remind you of a special date, start a  backup every
week  or let your computer fetch  your  email  during  the night, because of the
lower rates.

As with the System Preference Editors, there has  to be an additional program to
perform the settings made with TimeEvent.  This  program is  called cron and  it
runs in the background. 
@endnode


